title.narrative: Swaziland Health, HIV/AIDS and TB Project

description.narrative: The project development objectives (PDOs) are: (i) to improve access to and quality of health services in Swaziland with a particular focus on primary health care, maternal health and TB, and (ii) to increase social safety net access for OVC.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :IBRD 80190 | Description :Borrower shall prepare and furnish to the Bank for its approval an Annual Work Planand Budget, and an updated Procurement Plan containing all eligibleProject activities and expenditures planned for the followingFiscal Year | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :IBRD 80190 | Description :Borrower shall provide evidence, in form and substance satisfactory to the Bank, thatall MOH procurement staff have received and completed training in supply chain and health procurement within 12 months from theEffective Date. | Due Date :09-May-2013

Finance Agreement :IBRD 80190 | Description :Finalize the terms of reference for an external auditor, throughthe Auditor General'sOffice within 2months from the Effectiveness date | Due Date :02-Jul-2012

Finance Agreement :IBRD 80190 | Description :Recruit, no later than 6 months after the Effective Date, one procurement specialistand one FM specialist for the MOH PIT, all pursuant to terms of reference, qualification and experience acceptable to the Bank. |Due Date :09-Nov-2012

Finance Agreement :IBRD 80190 | Description :Recruit, no later than 6 months after the EffectiveDate, an external auditor,pursuant to terms of reference approved by the Bank,6 months after the Effectiveness date | Due Date :30-Nov-2012
Finance Agreement :IBRD 80190 | Description :Submit AnnualWork Plan and Budget for the first year of Project implementation within3 months fromthe Effective date | Due Date :31-Jul-2012
